 Here, `strict: false` avoids rebuilding the whole chain on the next build by disabling [strict mode](https://docs.buildstream.build/2.7/developing/strict-mode.html), and `override-project-caches: true` disables [remote cache](https://docs.buildstream.build/2.7/using_configuring_cache_server.html) lookups which, while helpful on the first build, can significantly slow down things on subsequent builds. By default, the cache is stored in `~/.cache/buildstream`. Note disabling the remote cache lookups will cause a slow fresh build from scratch without the caches the first time you run a `bst` command afterwards.
 
-For individual elements, you can also build them and, to inspect the result, check out the built artifact to a directory or drop into a runtime shell:
+For individual elements, you can also build them and inspect the result, either by checking out the built artifact to a directory or by dropping into a runtime shell:
 
 ```shell
 $ bst build core/gnome-shell.bst

